    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-03-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="285"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 343/50.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">German Chargé</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 71.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note No. 1034 of the 7th instant bringing to my notice the matter of the
                    transportation from Tangier to New York of Paul O. Stensland on board the
                    steamship <hi rend="italic">Prim Adalbert</hi> of the Hamburg-Amerika Line, and
                    to say in response that the representations which you make in this connection
                    with regard to alleged irregularity on the part of the American consul general
                    at Tangier will receive consideration.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
